This paper deals with the modeling and estimation of the electrical impedance behavior of lithium-ion batteries, which is a key aspect of battery management systems. The paper proposes a nonparametric approach to estimate the best linear approximation of the impedance from multiple datasets, which involves techniques from signal processing, machine learning, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which covers topics related to modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems. Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.ET (Embedded Systems), which are relevant to the methods and applications of the proposed approach.
